Injury accounts for up to 16% of the burden of disease. In non-conflict times that is traffic accidents (8th leading cause of death); of which 80% of deaths occur before people can get to a hospital. For our purposes the burden of disease is three to four times that (people are dropping bombs, shooting guns, and buildings are falling).

