| Prevent Insect Bites |

Many diseases, like malana and dengue, are spread through insect bites. One of the best protections is to prevent insect bites by:

• Using insect repellent (bug spray) with 30%-50% DEET. Picaridin, available in 7% and 15% concentrations, needs more frequent applicabon. There is less information available on how effective plcarldin is at protecting against all of the types of mosquitoes that transmit malaria.

• Wearing long-sleeved shirts, long pants, and a hat outdoors.

