After You Return Home

If you are not feeling well, you should see your doctor and mention that you have recently traveled.
Also tell your doctor if you were bitten or scratched by an animal while traveling.

If you have visited a malaria-nsk area, continue taking your antimalarial drug for 9 weeks (doxycycline
or mefloquine) or seven days (atovaquone/proguanil) after leaving the nsk area.

Malaria is always a serious disease and may be a deadly Illness. If you become ill with a fever or flu-like illness either while traveling in a malaria-nsk area or after you retum home (for up to I year), you should seek Immediate medical attention and should tell the physician your travel history.

